The '''Chief Minister of the Northern Territory''' is appointed by the [[Administrator of the Northern Territory of Australia|Administrator]], who in normal circumstances will appoint the head of whatever party holds the majority of seats in the legislature of the territory (in the [[Northern Territory]], the [[Legislative Assembly]]). However, in times of constitutional crisis the [[Administrator of the Northern Territory of Australia|Administrator]] can appoint someone else as Chief Minister. 

In [[Australia]], a [[Chief Minister]] is the [[head of government]] of a self-governing territory, while the head of government of a state is a [[Premiers of the Australian states|Premier]]. 

The incumbent Chief Minister of the Northern Territory is [[Paul Henderson (Australian politician)|Paul Henderson]], representing the [[Australian Labor Party]] since 2007.

