! style=&quot;background: #FFFFEF; color: #000000&quot; !  | [[Netherlands]]
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFCF; color: #000000&quot; !  | '''[[Arnhem]]'''
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFEF; color: #000000&quot; !  | ''[[Gelderland]]''
|-
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFEF; color: #000000&quot; !  | {{flagicon|Guyana}}
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFEF; color: #000000&quot; !  | [[Guyana]]
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFCF; color: #000000&quot; !  | -
! style=&quot;background: #FFFFEF; color: #000000&quot; !  | ''[[South America]]''
|}

The London Borough of Croydon is twinned with the [[municipality]] of Arnhem which is located in the east of the Netherlands.&lt;ref name=&quot;Arnhem Link&quot;&gt;{{cite web|year=2005|url=http://www.croydononline.org/history/places/arnhem.asp|title=Croydon and Arnhem Link|publisher=Croydon Online|accessdate=2007-09-27}}&lt;/ref&gt; The city of [[Arnhem]] is one of the [[List of cities in the Netherlands with over 100,000 people|10 largest cities in the Netherlands]]. They have been twinned since 1946 after both towns had suffered extensive bomb damage during the recently ended war. There is also a [[Guyana|Guyanese]] link supported by the council.&lt;ref name=&quot;Guyana&quot;&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.croydononline.org/community_information/list-fse.asp?wtT=2034|title=The community link with Guyana, South America|publisher=Croydon Online|accessdate=2007-09-28}}&lt;/ref&gt;

