* Murphy Justin D. and Matthew A. McNiece.[http://books.google.com/books?id=PW8kvG9wzTcC&amp;lpg=PA83&amp;dq=%22P-40%22%20Warhawk%20most%20produced&amp;pg=PA83#v=onepage&amp;q=%22P-40%22%20Warhawk%20most%20produced&amp;f=false ''Military aircraft, 1919-1945: An Illustrated History of their Impact.'' Santa Barbara, California: ABC-CLIO, 2009. ISBN 978-1851094981.
* Neulen, Hans Werner. [http://books.google.com/books?id=l-e4AAAACAAJ ''In the Skies of Europe: Air Forces Allied to the Luftwaffe, 1939–1945''] Ramsbury, Marlborough, UK: The Crowood Press, 2005. ISBN 1-86126-799-1.
* Pentland, Geoffrey. ''The P-40 Kittyhawk in Service''. Melbourne, Victoria, Australia: Kookaburra Technical Publications Pty. Ltd., 1974. ISBN 0-85880-012-8.
